  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <div class="faq">

    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>What exactly does your service cover?</summary>
      <p>
        I provide structured written documentation of live formal conferences, including proceedings,
        speaker summaries, session reports, and motion-and-resolution records. The output is designed for
        institutional reference, reporting, and archival use.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Do you provide photo or video coverage?</summary>
      <p>
        No. This service is focused exclusively on <strong>written institutional documentation</strong> of proceedings,
        discussions, and formal outcomes. It does not include photography, videography, or multimedia production.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="faq-item">
  <summary>What do you need from the client?</summary>

  <div class="faq-list">
    <p>Depending on the setup, I may require:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Event agenda or program flow</li>
      <li>List of speakers or officers</li>
      <li>Access to sessions</li>
      <li>Any reference materials for context</li>
      <li>Previous documentation for alignment</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</details>

    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>How is the documentation delivered?</summary>
      <p>
        Final outputs are typically provided in a structured document format (e.g., Word or PDF),
        organized by session or agenda item, depending on the scope of the event.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Can I request revisions?</summary>
      <p>
        Yes. Minor revisions for clarity, formatting, or corrections are included within reasonable scope
        after submission of the draft.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>How much are your services?</summary>
      <p>
        Rates range from ₱5,000 to ₱15,000 per day depending on the complexity and duration of the event.
      </p>
    </details>

    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Why is it not hourly-based?</summary>
      <p>
        Conference documentation requires continuous coverage across sessions. A per-day structure ensures
        complete and consistent documentation of the entire proceedings from start to finish.
      </p>
    </details>

